{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@preconcurrency","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"compactMap","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"ElementOfResult"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"transform","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"@Sendable","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"@escaping","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sci7ElementQa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Element","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/AsyncSequence\/Element"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"async"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sci12_ConcurrencyE10compactMapyAA020AsyncThrowingCompactC8SequenceVyxqd__Gqd__Sg7ElementQzYaKclF0H8OfResultL_qd__mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ElementOfResult"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/AsyncThrowingCompactMapSequence","text":"AsyncThrowingCompactMapSequence","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:12_Concurrency31AsyncThrowingCompactMapSequenceV"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sci12_ConcurrencyE10compactMapyAA020AsyncThrowingCompactC8SequenceVyxqd__Gqd__Sg7ElementQzYaKclF0H8OfResultL_qd__mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ElementOfResult"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An error-throwing mapping closure. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"accepts an element of this sequence as its parameter and returns a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"transformed value of the same or of a different type. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"throws an error, the sequence ends."}]}],"name":"transform"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An asynchronous sequence that contains, in order, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" elements produced by the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"text":" closure. The sequence","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ends either when the base sequence ends or when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"text":" throws an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"error.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"compactMap(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method to transform every element received from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a base asynchronous sequence, while also discarding any "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" results"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from the closure. Typically, you use this to transform from one type of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"element to another.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In this example, an asynchronous sequence called ","type":"text"},{"code":"Counter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" produces ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values from ","type":"text"},{"code":"1","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"code":"5","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The closure provided to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"compactMap(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method takes each ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and looks up a corresponding ","type":"text"},{"code":"String","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"romanNumeralDict","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" dictionary. Since there is no key for ","type":"text"},{"code":"4","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the closure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in this case, which ","type":"text"},{"code":"compactMap(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" omits from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"transformed asynchronous sequence. When the value is ","type":"text"},{"code":"5","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the closure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"throws ","type":"text"},{"code":"MyError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", terminating the sequence.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let romanNumeralDict: [Int: String] =","    [1: \"I\", 2: \"II\", 3: \"III\", 5: \"V\"]","","do {","    let stream = Counter(howHigh: 5)","        .compactMap { (value) throws -> String? in","            if value == 5 {","                throw MyError()","            }","            return romanNumeralDict[value]","        }","    for try await numeral in stream {","        print(numeral, terminator: \" \")","    }","} catch {","    print(\"Error: \\(error)\")","}","\/\/ Prints \"I II III Error: MyError() \""]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:Sci12_ConcurrencyE10compactMapyAA020AsyncThrowingCompactC8SequenceVyxqd__Gqd__Sg7ElementQzYaKclF::SYNTHESIZED::s:12_Concurrency31AsyncThrowingCompactMapSequenceV","title":"compactMap(_:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method